1.png" alt="" width="680" height="205" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1430422" srcset="https://cdn.wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/PowerPack-for-Beaver-Builder-is-now-WPML-compatible-1.png 680w, https://cdn.wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/PowerPack-for-Beaver-Builder-is-now-WPML-compatible-1-150x45.png 150w, https://cdn.wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/PowerPack-for-Beaver-Builder-is-now-WPML-compatible-1-300x90.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></a></p>\n<p>Many of our clients build their multilingual sites using the Beaver Builder plugin as it facilitates the process of designing their different website pages.</p>\n<p>Today we are happy to announce that the <a href="https://wpbeaveraddons.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">PowerPack for Beaver Builder</a> add-on is now WPML compatible. We would like to thank the PowerPack for Beaver Builder team for their cooperation.</p>\n<p>Now you can translate content from PowerPack for Beaver Builder using WPML. Check the multilingual demo <a href="http://power-pack-for-beaver-builder.compatibility.wpml.org/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">here</a>. </p>\n<p>We are working on integrating more Beaver Builder add-ons. Stay Tuned!</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=PQxwseNGfO4:rGAYiZBLOIs:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/PQxwseNGfO4" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit"